# grouping.rs (crates/steno/src/bin/viz_data)

Second build pass of the viz-data pipeline: takes the flat leaf list from pass one and buckets it by axis, splicing synthetic tree nodes (sections and axis-choice groupings) into the shared `node_order`/`nodes` maps, and resolves each `Category`'s root node list from the same bucketing.

The key non-obvious mechanic is the two-tier synthetic-node scheme. A `##>` comment marker produces a synthetic `sec:`-prefixed position (via `tree::position`/`section_parts`), recorded once per key in `LeafInputs::sections` in first-seen order via `record_section`'s dedup `HashSet`. These get materialized as real `Node`s only later, in `link_sections`, which must run *before* `apply_children` ‚Äî the ordering is load-bearing because `apply_children` copies `children_of` entries into nodes, and a section's own children only exist in `children_of` once `link_sections` has both created the node and linked it under its parent's children list.

Axis nodes (grouping by category/axis, e.g. tabs of variants) are synthetic too, appended after children are applied. Each axis node "mirrors" the preview fields (`terminal`, `multi_line`, `one_liner`, `children`, `description`, `one_liner_root`) of its *first choice's* node (`mirror_fields`), so a renderer that ignores the `axis` field still sees something reasonable ‚Äî this is intentional degrade-gracefully behavior, not a bug.

`leaves()` is the main pass-two entry: given `node_order`, a key‚Üírepresentative-entry map, and category/section markers, it produces one `Leaf` per node (computing its bucketing `position` from label+section) plus the deduped `Section` list. `apply_grouping()` is the actual mutator: takes `axis::Grouped` (children_of map + axes map) and the `sections` from `leaves()`, mutates `node_order`/`nodes` in place, and back-fills `cat.roots` for each `Category` by looking up `"cat:{label}"` in the same `children_of` map ‚Äî so category root resolution is entirely dependent on axis-bucketing having produced a `cat:`-prefixed key per category, a convention owned by the `axis`/`tree` modules, not visible here.

Depends on `crate::axis` (bucketing logic and `Leaf`/`Axis`/`Grouped` types), `crate::comments` (`Marker`, `label_for`, `section_for` ‚Äî parses `##>`-style source comments), and `crate::tree` (`Category`, `Node`, `position`, `section_parts` ‚Äî the node/position key format itself, e.g. `sec:` prefix parsing).